{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"91b0d06c-167e-4804-ac9d-bc88b383b8ff","content":"The official MCP Registry is the **[MCP Servers Registry](https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/servers)** on GitHub. To get your server listed:\n\n1. **Fork** the `modelcontextprotocol/servers` repo.\n2. **Add your server** entry to the registry (typically in `servers.json` or the relevant directory, following the existing format).\n3. **Open a Pull Request** against the main repo with:\n   - Server name, description, and category\n   - Link to your NuGet package\n   - Installation/usage instructions\n   - Source repo URL\n\n**Key tips:**\n- Review existing entries for the expected schema/format — the repo's `CONTRIBUTING.md` or `README.md` will have submission guidelines.\n- Make sure your NuGet package has a clear README, license, and proper metadata.\n\nYou can start here:  \n👉 https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/servers\n\nWould you like help drafting the registry entry or PR?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4fc081d2-3fbb-4143-b4f8-ddae0e25eaca","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to register their C# MCP server in the official MCP Registry. This is a general knowledge question about the MCP (Model Context Protocol) ecosystem. Let me provide what I know about this process.\n\nLet me check if there's any relevant information in the current working directory or if there are any docs related to MCP registry.","outputTokens":326,"requestId":"C022:3613B7:1C2339E:1FBD98B:6A07C208"},"id":"1326b2a1-6236-4b95-b8b0-52e7ee5019db","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:02:12.571Z","parentId":"efc1b4a0-a8bb-4a00-8fe9-e7adbc369801"}
